Text.LocalizedString: This is a test conversation created in order to facilitate importing Ability Card data into Unity via Dialogue System. 2.22.22

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: ""I need a way into this room.""

Text.LocalizedString: "I need a way into this room."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "The young man stands just in front..."

Text.LocalizedString: The young man stands just in front of the door to room 415, pointlessly brushing a gleaming vase with a frilly feather duster.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: ""You can help me by getting lost.""

Text.LocalizedString: "You can help me by getting lost."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "He glances at you furtively, but do..."

Text.LocalizedString: He glances at you furtively, but doesn't otherwise acknowledge your presence. The feathers in the duster appear to have been plucked from a peacock.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "He steps out of the way and gesture..."

Text.LocalizedString: He steps out of the way and gestures into the open room. "My sincerest apologies. Please let me know if I can be of help."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: ""If you don't leave right now," he..."

Text.LocalizedString: "If you don't leave right now," he mutters, "I'll be forced to ring for the security."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "“Sir, I already told you, I can’t l..."

Text.LocalizedString: “Sir, I already told you, I can’t let you in here.”

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: "You push into the room."

Text.LocalizedString: You push into the room.
[Charisma contest.] (Lie) “I just spoke to the concierge: a Mr. Gibson. It’s all taken care of, son. You can let me in.”

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "The young man narrows his eyes. "I..."

Text.LocalizedString: The young man narrows his eyes. "I don't believe that's true." He turns away from you.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: ""I'll come back later, then.""

Text.LocalizedString: "I'll come back later, then."
The Bellboy shuffles off, throwing back hurt glances.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: ""No, thank you, you can go.""

Text.LocalizedString: "No, thank you, you can go."

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Bellboy: "The Bellboy moves off quickly down..."

Text.LocalizedString: The Bellboy moves off quickly down the hall without a backward glance.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Ovidio Cabeaga: ""Yes, please wait here. I'll just b..."

Text.LocalizedString: "Yes, please wait here. I'll just be a moment."
The young man nods, spluttering, "Oh, I didn't realize you'd spoken to Mr. Gibson, sir." He fumbles for his keyring and unlocks the door.
